00:00:22.770 --> 00:00:27.210
Let's first start where
you decided to protest.

00:00:27.210 --> 00:00:28.560
When did you make that decision?

00:00:28.560 --> 00:00:31.000
And why did you
decide to do that?

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:34.620
Well, I protested in honor of
my daughter, Patti Sue Mathis,

00:00:34.620 --> 00:00:36.450
who was gay.

00:00:36.450 --> 00:00:38.920
She committed suicide.

00:00:38.920 --> 00:00:44.220
And I just said, I wonder
how Patti'd feel today.

00:00:44.220 --> 00:00:48.120
Here's a man running for
United States Senate who said

00:00:48.120 --> 00:00:50.850
that gay people are perverts.

00:00:50.850 --> 00:00:54.510
Gay people committing a
crime because they're gay.

00:00:54.510 --> 00:00:57.090
That's why I did what I did.

00:00:57.090 --> 00:00:59.220
I wanted people to
realize it's serious.

00:00:59.220 --> 00:01:02.400
A United States senator that
feels that way about people.

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:04.409
He's going to hold
his hand up and say,

00:01:04.409 --> 00:01:06.120
I uphold the Constitution.

00:01:06.120 --> 00:01:08.900
The Constitution said,
all men are created equal.

00:01:08.900 --> 00:01:10.650
And that's the way
they should be treated.

00:01:10.650 --> 00:01:14.137
Gay people have rights, just
like people who are not gay.

00:01:14.137 --> 00:01:16.572
[APPLAUSE]

00:01:27.290 --> 00:01:29.210
Well, Patti Sue
would be very, very--

00:01:29.210 --> 00:01:30.530
and is very proud of you.

00:01:30.530 --> 00:01:32.300
I can tell you that.

00:01:32.300 --> 00:01:34.970
And I know that you had a
hard time, at first, when

00:01:34.970 --> 00:01:36.860
she told you that she was gay.

00:01:36.860 --> 00:01:39.630
That was not an easy
thing for you to accept.

00:01:39.630 --> 00:01:42.080
And that, to me, makes
it even more beautiful

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:44.590
that you've turned
around your opinion.

00:01:44.590 --> 00:01:48.200
Well, due to teachings
I had as I grew up--

00:01:48.200 --> 00:01:50.675
when I found out Patti
was gay was the end

00:01:50.675 --> 00:01:52.160
of her senior year in school--

00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:53.810
and I showed my ass.

00:01:53.810 --> 00:01:55.100
I really did.

00:01:55.100 --> 00:01:57.320
And I regret it very much.

00:01:57.320 --> 00:02:01.712
About three months later,
Patti came to me and said,

00:02:01.712 --> 00:02:02.670
I don't want to be gay.

00:02:02.670 --> 00:02:04.090
Will you help me get some help?

00:02:04.090 --> 00:02:05.750
And so I said, sure.

00:02:05.750 --> 00:02:08.150
That shows you how naive I was.

00:02:08.150 --> 00:02:11.180
I made an appointment at
UAB Hospital in Birmingham.

00:02:11.180 --> 00:02:13.340
I took Patti up to the hospital.

00:02:13.340 --> 00:02:16.070
They did all kinds of
blood work on her that day.

00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:18.684
The doctor called
us in about 3:30.

00:02:18.684 --> 00:02:21.350
He said, young lady, there's not
a thing we can do about the way

00:02:21.350 --> 00:02:22.400
you are.

00:02:22.400 --> 00:02:23.780
There's nothing we can do.

00:02:23.780 --> 00:02:25.550
You're just who you are.

00:02:25.550 --> 00:02:27.980
And I said, man, this
doctor must be crazy.

00:02:27.980 --> 00:02:30.620
We took her to other
doctors, psychiatrists.

00:02:30.620 --> 00:02:32.860
Everyone told my
daughter, Patti,

00:02:32.860 --> 00:02:34.640
you can't help the way you are.

00:02:34.640 --> 00:02:37.560
That's what made me change.

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:41.970
Yeah, it's amazing that people
think that we're not supposed

00:02:41.970 --> 00:02:43.680
to be who we're born to be.

00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:47.370
And that we're supposed to
change to please other people.

00:02:47.370 --> 00:02:48.900
And I'm sorry that
your daughter--

00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:50.358
I'm sorry I didn't
get to meet her.

00:02:50.358 --> 00:02:52.950
I'm sorry that she didn't get
to see the world that we're

00:02:52.950 --> 00:02:55.710
living in now that gets better
and better because of people

00:02:55.710 --> 00:02:58.560
like you who are
opening up their minds.

00:02:58.560 --> 00:03:03.900
And you must be very
excited that this election

00:03:03.900 --> 00:03:05.130
went the way it did.

00:03:05.130 --> 00:03:07.350
I'm very excited it
went the way it did.

00:03:07.350 --> 00:03:10.970
The last thing we needed
was Roy Moore in Washington.

00:03:10.970 --> 00:03:13.630
Roy Moore needs to be somewhere
getting psychiatric help.

00:03:13.630 --> 00:03:14.830
That's where he needs to be.

00:03:14.830 --> 00:03:15.330
Yep.

00:03:15.330 --> 00:03:15.830
Yep.

00:03:15.830 --> 00:03:17.710
He does.

00:03:17.710 --> 00:03:18.210
Yep.

00:03:22.530 --> 00:03:25.020
Well, I know that this
was a big victory.

00:03:25.020 --> 00:03:26.190
There's a lot more to do.

00:03:26.190 --> 00:03:31.470
I think there's a lot of
stuff going on that I know--

00:03:31.470 --> 00:03:32.850
will you use your voice?

00:03:32.850 --> 00:03:33.870
Will you do this more?

00:03:33.870 --> 00:03:37.240
Because, I mean, look at
the attention you got.

00:03:37.240 --> 00:03:40.890
Well, see, I didn't have any
